samples.input: Who created the R programming language?

messages.content: Who created the R programming language?

content.text: R was created by Ross Ihaka and Robert Gentleman at the University of Auckland, New Zealand in the early 1990s. It was developed as an implementation of the S programming language with lexical scoping semantics. Since its initial development, R has grown through contributions from many statisticians and programmers worldwide, particularly through the R Core Team which now maintains the language.
